                            <comment id="16569750" author="paulk" created="Mon, 6 Aug 2018 05:27:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Eric, I think your analysis is correct. Did you have a scenario which triggered an error once the metadata was set to null?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16570256" author="emilles" created="Mon, 6 Aug 2018 14:17:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, I had a simple closure with a default value for a param.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;def closure = &lt;/p&gt;
{ one, two = 2 -&amp;gt;

}

&lt;p&gt;From there, I&apos;m not sure if it would be unset within an AST transform, but it was unset when visiting the AST in eclipse for purposes of semantic highlighting of the source.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="16570270" author="paulk" created="Mon, 6 Aug 2018 14:24:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It wouldn&apos;t normally be called from AST transforms. It would appear possible with joint compilation and static compilation together. I have already added the code change but didn&apos;t have a test. I think the idempotent code is safer anyway, so I&apos;ll close.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
